                  </hi> (<hi rend="italic">City policeman</hi>, 366.) On the 15th of July, about a quarter past twelve o'clock, I was in St. Paul's Churchyard, I saw the pri<lb></lb>soner followed him into Cheapside, and saw him follow a gentleman by Bow Churchyard—he took the gentleman's right coat pocket up with his right hand, and took the handkerchief out with his left—the gentleman got away, I did not know who he was—the prisoner told me he was in great distress.</p>
